      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/8138323.Janine_Myung_Ja">About Janine Myung Ja</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/8138323.Janine_Myung_Ja"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1508427073p3/8138323.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/8138323.Janine_Myung_Ja">Janine Myung Ja
</a></div>
<div class='goodreadsAuthorBadge'></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
784
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer17623096652531277685"><em></em><p>International multi-award recipient and gold-medalist author, Janine Myung Ja, Ph.D., is an adoption researcher, and rights-based activist for adopted people searching for long-lost families.</p><p>Janine and her twin sister are cofounders of Adoption Truth and Transparency Worldwide Network, one of the largest adoptee-led groups on social media. </p><p>Janine Myung Ja&apos;s soon-to-be-released political and histor</p></span>
  <span id="freeText17623096652531277685" style="display:none"><em></em><p>International multi-award recipient and gold-medalist author, Janine Myung Ja, Ph.D., is an adoption researcher, and rights-based activist for adopted people searching for long-lost families.</p><p>Janine and her twin sister are cofounders of Adoption Truth and Transparency Worldwide Network, one of the largest adoptee-led groups on social media. </p><p>Janine Myung Ja's soon-to-be-released political and history books include <em>Adoption What You Should Know, Adoptionized: A Critique of the Evangelical Orphan Movement</em>, and A<em>doptopia: A Deep Dive into the Life and Times of Adoptive Father, the Reverend Jim Jones.</em></p><p>Readers on Amazon and elsewhere have said this about Janine's work: "Insightful," "Important," "Awesome," "Great Understanding," "Highly Recommended," "Astonishing,"  and “Mind-Blowing."</p><p>Janine Myung Ja’s <em>Adoptionland: From Orphans to Activists</em> and <em>The “Unknown” Culture Club: Korean Adoptees, Then and Now</em> became Amazon bestsellers in the subcategories of Adoption, Women's History, and Minority Studies. Human-rights based readers and whistleblowers tend to appreciate her books the most due to their investigative nature into a lucrative industry controlled by adoptioneers. </p><p>Note: *Did you know that 100% of all adult adoptees in the United States and around the world surveyed in 2019 believed they should have access to their adoption documents and original birth certificates if they so wish? Janine Myung Ja’s books are rare investigations into the industry of intercountry and domestic adoption. The findings offer a bird’s eye view of the child market and are not recommended for fascists, proselytizers, neocolonialists, evangelical extremists, or stagnant closed-minded humans unwilling to accept evolutionary change.</p><em></em></span>
  <a data-text-id="17623096652531277685" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

